==English==
===Etymology===
Greek [[ορειβασια]], literally ‘mountain-treading’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /əɹeɪ'bæsɪə/

===Noun===
'''oreibasia'''
# a nocturnal ceremony of [[Bacchic]] women in ancient Greece
#:*'''1992''': Besides, it was getting cold.  They say that the '''''oreibasia''''' took place in midwinter, but I daresay the Peloponnesus is considerably milder that time of year than Vermont. — Donna Tartt, ''The Secret History''